>> ###
>>=20
>> The internet's technology revolution has arrived, and it is complete =
shit. Its attention economy has produced advanced analytics and machine =
intelligences which have self-evolved to capitalize on the discovery =
that people will spend their attention most willingly on outrage, and =
that markets can best be segmented through echo chambers. The result is =
a nation divided into as many subdivisions as can be algorithmically =
split to consume more attention.=20
>>=20
>> Meanwhile, new AI is developing at a breakneck pace, deepfakes are =
pole-vaulting over the uncanny valley, and quantum technology is about =
to put liquid nitrogen on the fire.
>>=20
>> But what we if did something different? What if we used the exact =
same cutting edge technologies being used today to encourage =
anti-vaxxers or protest to create cohesion, instead of division? What if =
we trained our AIs using dialogue and reason as measures of success? =
What if we had an AI have a conversation about the most contentious =
issues of our time with the most ardent, fanatical believers... and try =
to convince them otherwise?
>>=20
>> The USA is suffering a crisis of narrative. Nobody hears the others' =
side, so there's no dialogue possible. We each live in an artificial =
reality crafted by a legion of sales-oriented algorithms. But it doesn't =
have to be that way.=20
>>=20
>> We propose combining GPT-3, the most advanced language model in the =
world and the very first AI to produce text that's indistinguishable =
from a human's, with the most advanced market segmentation data modeling =
available, and use it to broker conversations online with every American =
who wants to. We'll set the system up to attempt to convince people that =
their unsubstantiated beliefs aren't true. With every exchange, be it =
via email or the website, the system will learn what is most convincing =
to whom.
>>=20
>> Then we'll pull out the most embelmatic dialogues and read them out =
on the show.
>>=20
>> That's where the magic happens. By presenting the AI as the =
apathetic, devilishly clever machine that it is we'll show that people =
are, in comparison, just that: only people. The more effective the AI is =
the more frightening its potential, and the greater the empathy with the =
ones who are being convinced. At the same time, the exchanges map a =
clear and relatable narrative for *how* to engage someone who believes =
in a flat earth. It shows, relatably and in an all-too-human way, =
exactly what's compelling or challenging to followers of QAnon.=20
>>=20
>> In short, it lets the AI be the bad guy, and gives Americans a =
narrative to reconciliation. It produces the ideal script for us to talk =
to each other over the issues that are dividing us most. It turns out =
weaknesses, as humans, into strengths we can use to heal our country.=20
>>=20
